### WhitsitTenx, This is just a thing I wrote for myself. Idk why you're here for an unfinished planet mod for KSP

A planet mod taking place during Kerbol's transformation into a red giant. Society has long forgotten the world around them. Based on Aethyl, a moon of Loone, a rapidly changing gas giant orbiting Aldhara. A large red giant going through it's mid life crisis. All might be fine for now, but the future of Jebediah Jr.'s children are at stake. With the kerbals forgetting everything they had known, they restart life on Aethyl. A world named after the few letters they could find in the ancient Lonapse textbooks. Pick yourself up and find a way out of this hellish system



### Mods required for this thing (I can't remember them all and I better not mess this up again)

-  WhitsitTenx, You should know this Fenton. Don't accidentally delete it again.
-  Kopernicus and it's dependencies, It's a planet mod. Of course you should have this installed idiot
-  Kopernicus expansion, this does some cool things
-  Niako Utils, this is the mitchel Netravali heitmap stuff. 
-  KSP Community Fixes, improves loading time a lot. 
-  KittopiaTech
-  Atmosphere Utils


### HIGHLY RECOMMENDED MODS/todo list for me

-  Scatterer, if you can't run this, you've got problems bud. Makes the game look a lot better. Even by itself and it has minimal performance impact
-  EVE Volumetrics/SVE/ whatever the dude calls this thing. V5 support only. It's also quite hideous at the moment. Its there though (edit: Aethyl looks decent. Only planet with support)
-  Firefly, minimal performcance impact, not supported yet. 
-  Texture Replacer, I've got a custom skybox. Please try it :)
-  Sigma Skyboxes, Skybox. I downloaded space engine for this 
-  ummm, some other stuff add later



